    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I made application to the Sultan for <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> to
                            visit Constantinople in order that I might have a consultation with
                            admiral, because the admiral requested me to do so. I know nothing of
                            his instructions; supposed he was authorized. Our war vessels have come
                            here since the <pb facs="0649" n="1383" xml:id="pg_1383"/> treaty which
                            closed Dardanelles. I had reason to believe that the <hi rend="italic">Marblehead’s</hi> coming would not be objected to by the treaty
                            Powers. Massacre Cæsarea. Americans safe.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
